cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new dataset and baseline models for Non-I.I.D. image classification, which involves dealing with data that is not identically and independently distributed (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of ConvNet models, which are a popular machine learning technique (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to create Non-I.I.D. contexts for the images, which could fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and evaluating the performance of the proposed models, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
